    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1963-07-31T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1963-07-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="353"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d353">
                <head>353. Memorandum From President <persName corresp="#p_KJF1" type="from"
                        >Kennedy</persName> to Secretary of Defense <persName corresp="#p_MRS1"
                        type="to">McNamara</persName>
                    <note n="0" type="source" xml:id="d353fn0">Source: <persName corresp="#p_KJF1"
                            >Kennedy</persName> Library, National Security Files, Portugal. Secret.
                        No drafting information appears on the source text.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1963-07-31">July 31, 1963</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>As the Portuguese situation may get increasingly complicated and as they may tend
                    to strike out at us as time goes on I think we should develop a contingency for
                    the loss of the Azores base. Will you give me your thoughts on this in
                    detail.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
